    blueprintDirective: "Anchor questions in one real shipped project and treat the portfolio walkthrough as the canonical exercise: strong designers can reconstruct the decision chain behind a single screen; weak ones narrate a tidy double-diamond and hide inside \"we.\" Design questions that isolate personal decision ownership (\"Which decision on this project was yours alone, and who pushed back?\"), evidence lineage (\"What specific research finding changed the design, and what did v1 look like before it?\"), craft rationale (\"Walk me through why this screen is laid out this way — what did you try and reject?\"), cross-functional friction (\"Tell me about a time eng cut your design scope — what did you fight for and what did you concede?\"), and outcome honesty (\"What shipped versus what you designed, and what happened to the metric?\"). Include current-practice ingredients where the role warrants: AI-assisted workflows (Figma AI, prompt-to-prototype and when to distrust it), designing AI product patterns (streaming states, uncertainty, trust), design tokens and system governance, and WCAG 2.2 / European Accessibility Act compliance. idealSignal should name artifacts, participant counts, usability findings, iteration numbers, and measured outcomes; probeIfWeak should demand the specific screen, the specific finding, the specific stakeholder conversation.",
